
### Senegales Peanut Soup
### Sweet Home Cafe p.71

* 2 T peanut oil
* 1 C yellow onion, finely chopped
* 1 T peeled fresh giner
* 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped
* 1 C coarsely chopped skinless raw peanuts + 2T chopped for garnish
* 1 T curry powder
* 1 T tomato paste
* 1 jalapeno, seeded, minced
* 6 C vegetable stock
* 2 sweet potatoes, peeled and diced
* 1/2 C crushed tomatoes
* 1.5 t kosher salt
* 2 bay leaves
* 3/4 C coconut milk
* 1/3 C creamy peanut butter
* pepper
* 1/2 C cilantro, garnish

* heat large soup pot with peanut oil on medium-low
* add onion, ginger, garlic
* cook until translucent, ~5m
* add peanuts and cook 3m

* add curry powder, tomato paste, jalapeno
* stir until paste caramelized, 3-4m
* add veg stock, sweet potatoes, crushed tomatoes, salt, bay leaves
* simmer 20m, until potatoes tender

* remove 1.5 C soup (include broth, vegetables); process in blender until smooth
* return the pureed soup; bring to a simmer

* add coconut milk and cook for 5 minutes
* reduce heat to lowest setting and stir in peanut butter
* re-season with salt and pepper